annotationA: FI02888p; ATP binding; DNA binding; protein binding; DNA ligase (ATP) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: telomere maintenance; DNA recombination; DNA biosynthetic process; nucleotide-excision repair; response to ionizing radiation; DNA ligation; DNA ligation involved in DNA repair; lagging strand elongation; double-strand break repair via nonhomologous end joining
annotationB: Flap endonuclease 1; Structure-specific nuclease with 5'-flap endonuclease and 5'-3' exonuclease activities involved in DNA replication and repair. During DNA replication, cleaves the 5'-overhanging flap structure that is generated by displacement synthesis when DNA polymerase encounters the 5'-end of a downstream Okazaki fragment. It enters the flap from the 5'-end and then tracks to cleave the flap base, leaving a nick for ligation.
